<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12120a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12120a">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12120a"> 120(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> water for <u>sa forme</u> to / purify se</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Jadis, &agrave;Noyal-Pontivy, aussit&ocirc;t qu&apos;une personne d&eacute;c&eacute;dait dans une maison, on s&apos;empressait d&apos;apporter un seau <mark>d&apos;eau, afin que son &acirc;me, <i><mark>sa forme</mark></i>, comme disent les bonnes gens, <mark>s&apos;y purifi&acirc;t</mark>, avant de partir vers l&apos;autre monde. <small> Fran&ccedil;ois Cadic, <a name="NCEL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#NCEL"><cite title="source">Nouveaux contes et l&eacute;gendes de Bretagne</cite></a> (1922) 57</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Great care is taken to keep all vessels filled with water, so that the soul does not try to purify itself in the milk, which it could cause to sour. </mm> </dd></dl>
